def StringToList(string):
    listOut = list(string.split(","))
    return listOut

def ListToString(listIn):
    stringOut = ""
    for value in listIn:
        stringOut = stringOut + str(value) + ", "

    return stringOut[:-2]

In [6]:
def dateConvert(dataframe):
    for colName in dataframe:
        try:
            if "date" in colName or "next" in colName:
                dataframe[colName] = pd.to_datetime(dataframe[colName])
            else:
                pass
        except TypeError:
            pass

    return dataframe

def coverageCalc(dataframe, colName):
    return round((len(dataframe[colName]) - dataframe[colName].isna().sum())/len(dataframe[colName])*100,2)

def meanCalc(dataframe, colName):
    try:
        tempVal = dataframe[colName].mean(skipna=True)
    except TypeError:
        tempVal = None

    try:
        tempVal = round(tempVal, 2)
    finally:
        return tempVal

def modeCalc(dataframe, colName):
    tempString = ""
    tempVal = 0

    try:
        tempVal = dataframe[colName].mode(dropna=True)
    except TypeError:
        tempString = None

    try:
        tempVal = round(tempVal, 2)
    except ValueError:
        pass
    except TypeError:
        pass

    try:
        if len(tempVal) < 5:
            tempList = []
            for indexNum in range(len(tempVal)):
                tempList.append(str(tempVal.iloc[indexNum]))
            tempString = " ,".join(tempList)
        else:
            tempString = f"{len(tempVal)} modes found"
    finally:
        return tempString



def minCalc(dataframe, colName):
    try:
        tempVal = dataframe[colName].min(skipna=True)
    except TypeError:
        tempVal = None

    try:
        tempVal = round(tempVal, 2)
    finally:
        return tempVal

def maxCalc(dataframe, colName):
    try:
        tempVal = dataframe[colName].max(skipna=True)
    except TypeError:
        tempVal = None

    try:
        tempVal = round(tempVal, 2)
    finally:
        return tempVal

def uniqueCalc(dataframe, colName):
    try:
        return round(dataframe[colName].nunique(),2)
    except TypeError:
        return None

def nonNullCalc(dataframe, colName):
    try:
        return round(dataframe[colName].count(),0)
    except TypeError:
        return None

def nullCalc(dataframe, colName):
    try:
        return round(dataframe[colName].isna().sum(),0)
    except TypeError:
        return None

def missingPercentage(number):
    return round(100-number,2)

def printHeadFull(inputVal):
    return inputVal.head(len(inputVal))

def showNaRows(dataframe, columnName, idCol, Type):
    if isinstance(idCol, list):
        if len(idCol) == dataframe.shape[1]:
            pass
        else:
            idCol.append(columnName)
        outDF = dataframe.loc[dataframe[columnName].isna()][idCol]
    else:
        outDF = dataframe.loc[dataframe[columnName].isna()][[idCol, columnName]]

    if Type.lower() == "head":
        return printHeadFull(outDF)
    elif Type.lower() == "return":
        return outDF

def modeWeight(dataframe, colName):
    try:
        modeValue = dataframe[colName].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False).reset_index()['index'][0]
        return str(round((len(dataframe[colName].loc[dataframe[colName] == modeValue])/len(dataframe)*100),2)) + "%"
    except Exception:
        return None
In [7]:
def subStringSelection(dataframe, subString, returnOption = "dataframe"):

    if returnOption.lower() == "dataframe":
        return dataframe.filter(regex=subString)
    elif returnOption.lower() == "columns":
        return [col for col in dataframe.columns if subString in col]
    else:
        raise ValueError("Wrong input for returnOption, possible values are dataframe/columns")

Summary Statistics Function¶

In [8]:
def summaryStatFunc(dataframe):
    tempDict = {}
    dataframe = dataframe.reset_index(drop=True)
    for columnName in dataframe:
        tempDict[columnName] = {"Type" : dataframe[columnName].dtypes.name,
                                "Coverage" : coverageCalc(dataframe,columnName),
                                "Mean" : meanCalc(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Mode" : modeCalc(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Min" : minCalc(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Max" : maxCalc(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Unique Values": uniqueCalc(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Non-Null Values": nonNullCalc(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Null Values": nullCalc(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Boolean Weights" : modeWeight(dataframe, columnName),
                                "Example" : [dataframe[columnName].iloc[random.randint(1,len(dataframe)-1)],
                                    dataframe[columnName].iloc[random.randint(1,len(dataframe)-1)],
                                    dataframe[columnName].iloc[random.randint(1,len(dataframe)-1)],
                                    dataframe[columnName].iloc[random.randint(1,len(dataframe)-1)],
                                    dataframe[columnName].iloc[random.randint(1,len(dataframe)-1)]]}


    outDF = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(tempDict, orient="index")

    return outDF

def missingMarkdownGenerator(dataframe):

    temporaryDataFrame = summaryStatFunc(dataframe)
    temporaryDataFrame = temporaryDataFrame.loc[temporaryDataFrame["Coverage"] < 100].sort_values(by ="Coverage")

    missingValDF = temporaryDataFrame.Coverage.value_counts()
    missingValDF = pd.DataFrame(missingValDF)
    missingValDF.reset_index(inplace=True)
    missingValDF = missingValDF.sort_values(by = "index", ascending= False)

    out_string = f"There are {len(temporaryDataFrame)} columns with missing observations. \n"

    for row in missingValDF.iterrows():
        funcCounter =+ 1
        if row[1][1] > 1:
            if row[1][1] > 3:
                col_list = temporaryDataFrame[temporaryDataFrame['Coverage'] == row[1][0]].index.values

                nestCounter = 1
                colString = ""
                listCounter = 1
                cutoffVal = 3

                for iteration in col_list:
                    if nestCounter % (cutoffVal+1) == 0:
                        colString = colString + iteration + ",* \n"
                    elif nestCounter % (cutoffVal+1) == 1:
                        colString = colString  + f"   {listCounter}. " + "*"+ iteration + " "
                        listCounter += 1
                        if iteration == col_list[-1]:
                            colString = colString[:-1] + "*"
                    elif iteration == col_list[-1]:
                        colString = colString + iteration + "*"
                    else:
                        colString = colString + iteration + ", "
                    nestCounter += 1




                out_string = out_string + f"{funcCounter}. {int(row[1][1])} columns are missing ***{missingPercentage(row[1][0])}%*** of observations (actual = {int(round(len(df) * missingPercentage(row[1][0])/100,0))}) " \
                                        f"columns : \n {colString} \n"
            else:
                col_list = temporaryDataFrame[temporaryDataFrame['Coverage'] == row[1][0]].index.values
                out_string = out_string + f"{funcCounter}. {int(row[1][1])} columns are missing ***{missingPercentage(row[1][0])}%*** of observations (actual = {int(round(len(df) * missingPercentage(row[1][0])/100,0))}) | columns = *{', '.join(col_list)}* \n"
        else:
            col_list = temporaryDataFrame[temporaryDataFrame['Coverage'] ==  row[1][0]].index.values
            out_string = out_string + f"{funcCounter}. {int(row[1][1])} column is missing ***{missingPercentage(row[1][0])}%*** of observations (actual = {int(round(len(df) * missingPercentage(row[1][0])/100,0))}) | columns = *{', '.join(col_list)}* \n"

    if len(missingValDF) == 0:
        pass
    else:
        out_string = out_string + "\nOf the columns with missing values ;"

    listCounter = 1
    if len([i for i in temporaryDataFrame.index.values if 'percentage_diff' in i]) > 0:
        out_string = out_string + f"\n {listCounter}. The *{' ,'.join([i for i in temporaryDataFrame.index.values if 'percentage_diff' in i])}* columns are ***calculated*** columns and can be cleaned by using imputation of 0's to mitigate divide by 0 errors."
        listCounter += 1
    if len(temporaryDataFrame[temporaryDataFrame['Coverage'] > 2].index.values) > 0:
        out_string = out_string + f"\n {listCounter}. The *{' ,'.join(temporaryDataFrame[temporaryDataFrame['Coverage'] < 98].index.values)}* columns are ***sourced*** columns for these we need to look at either imputation or removal."

    out_string = out_string + f"\n\n Overall coverage is good on ***{100- round(len(temporaryDataFrame)/len(df)*100,2)}%*** of columns. This will give enough information to commence machine learning"

    return out_string, missingValDF

def missingValueMarkDownGenerator(dataframe, missingCol, otherColumns):
    if isinstance(otherColumns, str):
        if otherColumns == "all":
            otherColumns = dataframe.columns.values.tolist()
        elif otherColumns != "acctrefno":
            otherColumns = [otherColumns, "acctrefno"]
        else:
            otherColumns = [otherColumns]
    else:
        if "acctrefno" not in otherColumns:
            otherColumns.append("acctrefno")

    missingRowsDF = showNaRows(dataframe, missingCol, otherColumns, "return")
    missingAcctrefno = missingRowsDF.acctrefno.unique()
    try:
        if len(missingAcctrefno) == 1:
            outString = f"The account number of missing values in *{missingCol}* is ***{' ,'.join(map(str, missingAcctrefno))}***. In this instance the missing values covers ***{round(len(missingRowsDF) / len(df.loc[(df['acctrefno'].isin(missingAcctrefno))]) * 100, 2)}%*** of the account observations. Since the missing values cover only one account and ***{round(len(missingRowsDF) / len(dataframe) * 100, 2)}%*** "
        elif len(missingAcctrefno) == 0:
            outString = f"No missing value found in column *{missingCol}*"
        elif len(missingAcctrefno) > 5:
            outString = f"There are ***{len(missingAcctrefno)}*** account numbers with missing values in *{missingCol}*. In this instance the missing values cover ***{round(len(missingRowsDF) / len(df.loc[(df['acctrefno'].isin(missingAcctrefno))]) * 100, 2)}%*** of the account observations. Since the missing values cover multiple accounts and ***{round(len(missingRowsDF) / len(dataframe) * 100, 2)}%*** "
        else:
            outString = f"The account numbers of missing values in *{missingCol}* are ***{' ,'.join(map(str, missingAcctrefno))}***. In this instance the missing values cover ***{round(len(missingRowsDF) / len(df.loc[(df['acctrefno'].isin(missingAcctrefno))]) * 100, 2)}%*** of the account observations. Since the missing values cover multiple accounts and ***{round(len(missingRowsDF) / len(dataframe) * 100, 2)}%*** "

        if round(len(missingRowsDF)/len(dataframe)*100,2) >= 1 or round(len(missingRowsDF) / len(df.loc[(df['acctrefno'].isin(missingAcctrefno))]) * 100,2) <= 50:
            outString = outString + "of the dataset we need to investigate further."
        else:
            if len(missingAcctrefno) == 1:
                outString = outString + "of the dataset we can delete this account reference instead of the column(s) with missing values."
            else:
                outString = outString + "of the dataset we can delete these account references instead of the column(s) with missing values."
    except ZeroDivisionError:
        outString = f"There are ***0 missing value in {missingCol}***."

    return outString, missingAcctrefno, missingRowsDF

Markdown Bullet Point creator¶

In [11]:
def markdownBulletCreator(listIn, outString):
    funcCounter = 1
    for listItem in listIn:
        outString = outString + f"{funcCounter}. {listItem} \n"
        funcCounter += 1
    return outString

def markdownBulletCreatorDict(dictIn, outString):
    funcCounter = 1
    for k, v in dictIn.items():
        outString = outString + f"{funcCounter}. {k} = {v} \n"
        funcCounter += 1

    return outString

New column Creator¶

In [12]:
def newColumnCreator(dataFrame, sourceColumn, valueOne, operatorOne, evalMode = "and", valueTwo = None, operatorTwo = None, imputeTrue = True, imputeFalse = False, overwriteCol = False):
    outList = []

    for indexVal in range(len(dataFrame)):
        rowValue = dataFrame[str(sourceColumn)][indexVal]

        try:
            if operatorTwo is None:
                evalString = f"{rowValue} {operatorOne} {valueOne}"
            else:
                evalString = f"{rowValue} {operatorOne} {valueOne} {evalMode} {rowValue} {operatorTwo} {valueTwo}"
        except Exception as error:
            raise Exception(error)

        if eval(evalString):
            outList.append(imputeTrue)
        else:
            if imputeFalse == "Value":
                outList.append(rowValue)
            else:
                outList.append(imputeFalse)

    if overwriteCol:
        dataFrame[str(sourceColumn)] = outList
    else:
        return outList

def densityPlot (dataFrame, colName, graphTitle = None):
    if graphTitle is None:
        graphTitle = f"Density plot of {colName}"
    else:
        pass

    sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(6,4),"font.size":10,"axes.titlesize":15,"axes.labelsize":10, 'xtick.labelsize':7, 'ytick.labelsize':7})
    sns.set_style('whitegrid')
    sns.kdeplot(data = np.array(dataFrame[colName]), color = "#23ec12").set_title(label=graphTitle)

def barPlot (dataFrame, colName, graphTitle = None):
    if graphTitle is None:
        graphTitle = f"Count plot of {colName}"
    else:
        pass

    sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(6,4),"font.size":10,"axes.titlesize":15,"axes.labelsize":10, 'xtick.labelsize':7, 'ytick.labelsize':7})
    sns.set_style('whitegrid')
    ax = sns.barplot(data = dataFrame[colName].value_counts().reset_index(), palette= sns.color_palette(["#23ec12", "#0d5d06"]), x = "index", y = colName, saturation = 1)
    ax.set_title(label=graphTitle)
    ax.bar_label(ax.containers[0])
In [15]:
def barPlotCompare (dataFrameOne, dataFrameTwo, graphTitle = None, keyOne = "yTrain", keyTwo = "yTest"):

    dataDicts = [dataFrameTwo.value_counts(), dataFrameOne.value_counts()]
    result = pd.concat(dataDicts, keys=[keyOne, keyTwo]).reset_index()
    result = result.rename(columns = {result.columns[0] : "Source", result.columns[1] : "Value", result.columns[2] : "Counts"})

    if graphTitle is None:
        graphTitle = f"Count plot comparing test and train"
    else:
        pass

    sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(6,4),"font.size":10,"axes.titlesize":15,"axes.labelsize":10, 'xtick.labelsize':7, 'ytick.labelsize':7})
    sns.set_style('whitegrid')
    ax = sns.barplot(data = result, palette= sns.color_palette(["#23ec12", "#0d5d06"]), x = "Value", y = "Counts", hue = "Source", saturation = 1)
    ax.set_title(label=graphTitle)
    for container in ax.containers:
        ax.bar_label(container)
In [16]:
def confusionMatrix(yPrediction, yActual, returnOption = "graph"):
    confusion_matrix = pd.crosstab(yActual, yPrediction, rownames=['Actual'], colnames=['Predicted'])

    if returnOption.lower() == "dataframe":
        return pd.DataFrame(confusion_matrix)
    elif returnOption.lower() == "graph":
        group_names = ['True Neg','False Pos','False Neg','True Pos']
        group_counts = ["{0:0.0f}".format(value) for value in confusion_matrix.values.flatten()]
        group_percentages = ["{0:.2%}".format(value) for value in confusion_matrix.values.flatten()/np.sum(confusion_matrix.values)]

        labels = [f"T: {v1}\n N: {v2} \n W: {v3}" for v1, v2, v3 in zip(group_names,group_counts,group_percentages)]
        labels = np.asarray(labels).reshape(2,2)

        sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(6,4),"font.size":10,"axes.titlesize":15,"axes.labelsize":10, 'xtick.labelsize':7, 'ytick.labelsize':7})
        sns.set_style('whitegrid')
        ax = sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix, annot=labels, fmt='', cmap=sns.color_palette(["#23ec12", "#0d5d06", "#23ec12", "#0d5d06"]), linewidths= 0.5, linecolor= "white", cbar = False,
                         annot_kws= {'fontstyle': 'italic', 'color':'white', 'alpha': 1})
        ax.set_title("Confusion Matrix of Actual vs Predicted")
In [17]:
def corrMatrix(dataframe, showOption = True, returnOption = True, size = (15,10), graphTitle = None):

    if graphTitle is None:
        graphTitle = f"Correlation Matrix"
    else:
        pass

    corrMatrixArray = dataframe.corr()
    corrMatrixDF = pd.DataFrame(corrMatrixArray)

    corrFeatures = set()

    for i in range(len(corrMatrixArray.columns)):
        for j in range(i):
            if abs(corrMatrixArray.iloc[i, j]) > 0.9: #Checks for -0.9 and 0.9 high correlations .
                colName = corrMatrixArray.columns[i]
                corrFeatures.add(colName)

    if showOption:
        filtered_cor = corrMatrixArray[corrMatrixArray>=.9]
        plt.figure(figsize=size)
        sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(6,4),"font.size":10,"axes.titlesize":15,"axes.labelsize":10, 'xtick.labelsize':7, 'ytick.labelsize':7})
        sns.set_style('whitegrid')
        sns.heatmap(filtered_cor, cmap="Greens", linewidths=0.05, linecolor='#F0F0F0').set_title(graphTitle)
    else:
        pass

    if returnOption:
        return corrMatrixDF, corrFeatures
    else:
        pass
In [18]:
def linePlot (dataFrame, colName, hue = None, graphTitle = None, xLabel = None, yLabel = None, figSize = None, setAxis = True, splitLine = False):
    if graphTitle is None:
        graphTitle = f"Count plot of {colName}"
    if xLabel is None:
        xLabel = "index"
    if yLabel is None:
        yLabel = colName
    if figSize is None:
        figSize = (6, 4)

    if splitLine:
        concatDf = pd.DataFrame({"index": list(range(max(dataFrame["index"]))),
                    hue: ["Guide"] * max(dataFrame['index']),
                    colName : [((max(dataFrame[colName]) - min(dataFrame[colName])) / 2) + min(dataFrame[colName])] * max(dataFrame['index'])})

        dataFrame = pd.concat([dataFrame, concatDf])


    sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':figSize, "font.size":10, "axes.titlesize":15, "axes.labelsize":10, 'xtick.labelsize':7, 'ytick.labelsize':7})
    sns.set_style('whitegrid')
    ax = sns.lineplot(data = dataFrame, palette = sns.color_palette(["#23ec12", "#0d5d06", "#787878"]), x = "index", y = colName, hue = hue)
    ax.set(xlabel = xLabel, ylabel = yLabel)
    if setAxis:
        ax.set(xticks=np.arange(min(dataFrame["index"]),max(dataFrame["index"])+1,1))
        if max(dataFrame["index"] > 20):
            ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MultipleLocator(int(max(dataFrame["index"]/10))))
    else:
        pass
    ax.set_title(label=graphTitle)

As we can see the fico score is 0 after internal discussion is has been determined that this value is not an error. Some people simply have no FICO score, to model this we will take two steps:

  1. We will set 0 fico to the average FICO.
  2. We will create a boolean variable called No_FICO where users have a fico of 0 get a 1 the others will get a 0.

recalculate percentage_diff_app_fico¶
In [38]:
resultList = []

df["AppFICO"] = df["fico"] + df["CoAppFICO"]

for x in range(len(df)):
    if not df["coApp"][x]:
        resultList.append(100.00) #If there is no co-app the FICO coverage is always 100
    elif df["fico"][x] == 0 and df["CoAppFICO"][x] == 0 and df["coApp"][x] == True:
        resultList.append(50.00) #if there is a co-app but both numbers are 0 we have an edge case
    elif df["CoAppFICO"][x] == 0:
        resultList.append(100.00) #if the FICO of the co-app is 0 the applicant always covers 100% of the FICO
    else:
        resultList.append(round((df["AppFICO"][x] - df["fico"][x]) / df["AppFICO"][x] * 100,2))

df["percentage_diff_app_fico"] = resultList

Target Variable¶

In [48]:
outDict = {}

__counter = 0
for x in sorted(list(df["transaction_code"].value_counts().index)):
    uniqueDF = df.transaction_description[(df.transaction_code == x)].unique()
    for y in uniqueDF:
        outDict[__counter] = [x, y]
        __counter += 1

Creation of paid Boolean¶

Here we create the prediction target, a boolean which shows if a customer has paid on time.

In [50]:
lateList = []
for x in range(len(df)):
    if df["date_due"][x].date() < df["transaction_date"][x].date():
        lateList.append(0)
    else:
        lateList.append(1)
df["paid"] = lateList

Creation of payments days late¶

This variable is another prediction option but for now is just used for validation, it will later be dropped.

In [51]:
lateList = []
for x in range(len(df)):
    if df["date_due"][x].date() < df["transaction_date"][x].date():
        lateList.append((df["transaction_date"][x].date() - df["date_due"][x].date()).days)
    else:
        lateList.append(0)
df["payment_days_late"] = lateList

Textual explanation regarding variables with high unique counts¶

In this section we will look at variables with high N counts. This means that these variables have a lot of different variables in them. This isn't a problem if a variable holds linear information but the variables who don't need to be removed.

Account specific variables¶

First we have a number of account specific variables. These variables do not hold any information except to tie accounts to each other. We will remove these variables. The account specific variables are:

  1. current_note_amount

  2. loan_balance_total

    ##### Transaction specific variables

    The next set of variables are transaction specific. While there are some samples available in these variables they will be so small they will merely introduce bias and noise. They will also hold no statistical significance. The transaction specific variables are:

  3. transrefno
  4. transaction_date

  5. date_due

    ##### Small sub-sample sizes

    The last set of variables have small sub-sample sizes. The variables listed below hold no linear numeric information and therefore will be removed. A variable like zipcode for example where 84106 is not better then 84105 will be removed. The transaction specific variables are:

  6. value_price_diff

  7. zip

    ##### Non Dropped Variables

    The last set of variables we will keep for various reasons listed below. The variables listed below hold no linear numeric information and therefore will be removed. A variable like zipcode for example where 84106 is not better then 84105 will be removed. Value_price_diff will also be removed since it can be calculated from loan_balance_average and origional value and will introduce bias when kept. The kept variables are:

  8. acctrefno: Is the accountID we will need this for future reference [Reference Column]
  9. loan_balance_average: Shows the value of the loan [Linear Information]
  10. transaction_amount: Shows the amount the client has to pay in the month[Linear Information]
  11. original_miles: Shows the miles of the vehicle for which the loan has been taken out[Linear Information]
  12. original_value: Shows the original value of the vehicle [Linear Information]
Drop variables with high unique Counts¶

Removal of date variables¶

Date variables hold no information since we want to create statistical profiles for each profile and omit any timeseries analysis. Additionally, transaction_date and date_due are the origin of the target variable and therefore hold the actual information of the target which will provide the model with the answer. All date variables will be removed for the aforementioned reasons.

If needed in the future we can engineer these variables to hold linear information like date differences.

In [79]:
max_neighbours = 10
step_size = 1

bestOos = 0
bestNeighbours = 0

scoreOos = []
scoreIs = []


for x in range(1, max_neighbours+1, step_size):
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=x)
    knn.fit(xTrain, yTrain)

    # In Sample
    yPredOos = knn.predict(xTest)
    accOos = accuracy_score(yTest, yPredOos)

    # Out of sample
    yPredIs = knn.predict(xTrain)
    accIs = accuracy_score(yTrain, yPredIs)

    # append to dict
    scoreOos.append(accOos)
    scoreIs.append(accIs)


    # Update Output
    if accOos > bestOos:
        if accIs > .95:
            pass
        else:
            bestOos = accOos
            bestNeighbours = x

knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=bestNeighbours)
knn.fit(xTrain, yTrain)

yPredIs = knn.predict(xTrain)
yPredOos = knn.predict(xTest)

md(f"The accuracy of the model with {bestNeighbours} Neighbours is ***{round(accuracy_score(yTest, yPredOos) * 100, 2)}%*** for out-of-sample and ***{round(accuracy_score(yTrain, yPredIs) * 100, 2)}%*** for in-sample")
Out[79]:

The accuracy of the model with 3 Neighbours is 77.59% for out-of-sample and 87.8% for in-sample

GridSearching¶

In [84]:
# paramGrid = {"n_estimators" : list(range(800,1400,200)),
#               "max_depth" : list(range(3,8,1)),
#               "alpha" : [0.1,0.5],
#               "learning_rate" : [0.1],
#               "colsample_bytree" : [0.8,0.5],
#               "lambda" : [1],
#               "subsample": [1]}

paramGrid = {"n_estimators" : list(range(800,1200,200)),
              "max_depth" : list(range(4,7,1)),
              "alpha" : [0.5],
              "learning_rate" : [0.1],
              "colsample_bytree" : [0.8],
              "lambda" : [1],
              "subsample": [1]}

paramGrid = pd.DataFrame(ParameterGrid(paramGrid))

kf = KFold(n_splits=3, shuffle=True, random_state=42)

counter = 0
xgboost_timer_start = timeit.default_timer()
optimalAucFold = 0
optimalAccFold = 0
verboseDict = {}
optimalParamDict = {}
for epoch in range(len(paramGrid)):

    xgboost_timer_lap= timeit.default_timer()
    # Run Model
    xgRegressor = xgb.XGBClassifier(objective ='binary:logistic',
                                   n_estimators = paramGrid["n_estimators"][epoch],
                                   max_depth = paramGrid["max_depth"][epoch],
                                   reg_alpha = paramGrid["alpha"][epoch],
                                   learning_rate = paramGrid["learning_rate"][epoch],
                                   colsample_bytree = paramGrid["colsample_bytree"][epoch],
                                   reg_lambda = paramGrid["lambda"][epoch],
                                   subsample = paramGrid["subsample"][epoch],
                                   verbosity = 0,
                                   use_label_encoder=False)


    accFold = []
    aucFold = []
    try:
        for Train_index, Test_index in kf.split(xTrain, yTrain):
            xTrainFold, xTestFold = xTrain.iloc[Train_index], xTrain.iloc[Test_index]
            yTrainFold, yTestFold = yTrain.iloc[Train_index], yTrain.iloc[Test_index]
            xgRegressor.fit(xTrainFold, yTrainFold)

            yTestFoldPred = xgRegressor.predict(xTestFold)
            accFold.append(accuracy_score(yTestFold, yTestFoldPred))
            aucFold.append(roc_auc_score(yTestFold, yTestFoldPred))

        meanFoldAcc = np.mean(accFold)
        meanFoldAuc = np.mean(aucFold)

    except Exception as e:
        raise Exception(e)

    if meanFoldAuc > optimalAucFold:
        optimalAucFold = meanFoldAuc
        optimalAccFold = meanFoldAcc
        optimalParamDict = {"objective" : 'binary:logistic',
                            "n_estimators" : paramGrid["n_estimators"][epoch],
                             "max_depth" : paramGrid["max_depth"][epoch],
                             "reg_alpha" : paramGrid["alpha"][epoch],
                             "learning_rate" : paramGrid["learning_rate"][epoch],
                             "colsample_bytree" : paramGrid["colsample_bytree"][epoch],
                             "reg_lambda" : paramGrid["lambda"][epoch],
                             "subsample": paramGrid["subsample"][epoch],
                              "verbose" : 0}

    counter += 1
    xgboost_timer_stop = timeit.default_timer()

    if counter % 100 == 0 or counter == 1 or counter == len(paramGrid):
        print(f"Epoch {counter}/{len(paramGrid)} | time elapsed = {str(datetime.timedelta(seconds = round(xgboost_timer_stop - xgboost_timer_start,0)))}, "
              f"estimated time remaining {str(datetime.timedelta(seconds = round((xgboost_timer_stop - xgboost_timer_lap) * (len(paramGrid) - counter),0)))}")
    else:
        pass

    epochParamGrid = {"Mean Fold Accuracy": meanFoldAcc,
                      "Mean Fold Auc": meanFoldAuc,
                      "n_estimators": paramGrid["n_estimators"][epoch],
                      "max_depth": paramGrid["max_depth"][epoch],
                      "reg_alpha": paramGrid["alpha"][epoch],
                      "learning_rate": paramGrid["learning_rate"][epoch],
                      "colsample_bytree": paramGrid["colsample_bytree"][epoch],
                      "reg_lambda": paramGrid["lambda"][epoch],
                      "subsample": paramGrid["subsample"][epoch]}
    
    verboseDict[epoch+1] = epochParamGrid

Epoch 1/6 | time elapsed = 0:00:20, estimated time remaining 0:01:39
Epoch 6/6 | time elapsed = 0:02:46, estimated time remaining 0:00:00

False Positives¶

False Positives are the most detrimental to the implentation of the model. We want to call people that are not going to pay and a false positive would prevent that, so we will further investigate the profiles of false positives.

In [96]:
falsePositiveOos = xTest
falsePositiveOos['predicted'] = yPredOos
falsePositiveOos['actual'] = yTest
falsePositiveOos = falsePositiveOos[(falsePositiveOos['predicted'] != falsePositiveOos['actual']) & (falsePositiveOos['predicted'] == 1)]

actualPositiveOos = xTest
actualPositiveOos['predicted'] = yPredOos
actualPositiveOos['actual'] = yTest
actualPositiveOos = actualPositiveOos[(actualPositiveOos['predicted'] == actualPositiveOos['actual']) & (actualPositiveOos['predicted'] == 1)]

compareDF1 = summaryStatsFalsePos.drop(["Unique Values", "Non-Null Values", "Example"], axis = 1)

comparedDF.columns.set_levels(['False','Actual','Variables'],level=1, inplace = True)
treshold = 25

def highlight_cells(dataframe):
    color = 'background-color: #23ec12'
    df1 = pd.DataFrame('', index=dataframe.index, columns=dataframe.columns)
    for x in range(len(dataframe)):
        for y in [1,3,5,7,9]:
            if "%" in str(dataframe.iloc[x,y]):
                temp1 = str(dataframe.iloc[x,y+1][:-1])
                temp2 = str(dataframe.iloc[x,y][:-1])
                if abs((float(temp1) - float(temp2)) / float(temp1))*100 > treshold:
                    df1.iloc[x,y] = color
            elif isinstance(dataframe.iloc[x,y], str):
                pass
            elif (dataframe.iloc[x, y] == 0) | (dataframe.iloc[x, y + 1] == 0):
                pass
            else:
                if abs((dataframe.iloc[x,y+1] - dataframe.iloc[x,y]) / dataframe.iloc[x,y+1])*100 > treshold:
                    df1.iloc[x,y] = color

    return df1

display(HTML("<div style='height: 500px'>" + comparedDF.style.set_table_styles(table_styler).format(precision = 2).hide_index().apply(highlight_cells, axis=None).set_caption(f"Differences between False Positives and Actual Positives at a treshold of {treshold}%").render() + "</div>"))
